Equation 7.36 indicates that after the switch has been closed, the current grows exponentially from zero to a final value of \(\frac{V_{s}}{R}\). The circuit's time constant, \(L / R\), dictates the rate of this growth. After one time constant, the current attains approximately \(63.2\%\) of its ultimate value, a characteristic of first-order systems.

